<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
A single series of this species was collected in a rainwater pool formed in exposed rocks in the Orinoco floodplain (Fig. 29). It was taken together with hundreds of specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Berosus garciai" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garciai">Berosus garciai</taxonomicName>
sp. n. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Berosus ruffinus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruffinus">Berosus ruffinus</taxonomicName>
was previously recorded from Venezuela, also along the Orinoco slightly further downriver (
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva, A" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royale Belge d'Entomologie" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="183 - 230" title="Some types of Berosus (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae) kept in the collections of the Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique." volume="129" year="1993">Oliva 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
